Malpractice and Embezzlement</font></i>

30
00:01:52.529 --> 00:01:53.947
{\an8}<i><font color="#ffa07a">Jou-ri</font></i>

31
00:01:55.782 --> 00:01:58.844
{\an8}Unbeknownst to me, these
articles are making headlines.

32
00:01:58.868 --> 00:02:03.432
{\an8}I wonder what tomorrow's headline will bring.

33
00:02:03.456 --> 00:02:06.310
{\an8}I'll find out who's behind this.

34
00:02:06.334 --> 00:02:08.786
{\an8}No need for that. It's obvious.

35
00:02:08.837 --> 00:02:11.023
{\an8}What's the first thing politicians do...

36
00:02:11.047 --> 00:02:13.067
{\an8}when they gain power?

37
00:02:13.091 --> 00:02:15.459
{\an8}They go after companies like mine.

38
00:02:15.802 --> 00:02:18.781
{\an8}What can I do? The
presidential election is coming up.

39
00:02:18.805 --> 00:02:22.284
They have to create a distraction
if they want to save themselves.

40
00:02:22.308 --> 00:02:26.247
Still, they crossed the line. Don't you think?

41
00:02:26.271 --> 00:02:30.084
Why did they use such
an unflattering photo of me?

42
00:02:30.108 --> 00:02:31.085
Darn it.

43
00:02:31.109 --> 00:02:33.644
Look at that double chin.

44
00:02:34.112 --> 00:02:35.688
Gosh.

45
00:02:38.032 --> 00:02:39.942
Don't worry, sir.

46
00:02:40.118 --> 00:02:42.486
I'll take care of it.

47
00:02:42.579 --> 00:02:44.780
Right. And...

48
00:02:48.793 --> 00:02:51.230
This is my husband's old phone.

49
00:02:51.254 --> 00:02:54.358
There's a recording of a call he
had with Woobyeok Construction.

50
00:02:54.382 --> 00:02:56.542
Do you want to be my son?

51
00:03:06.269 --> 00:03:08.053
Sorry?

52
00:03:08.646 --> 00:03:11.333
I'd really love that.

53
00:03:11.357 --> 00:03:16.478
How great would it be if
I had a reliable son like you?

54
00:03:17.030 --> 00:03:20.259
Then I'd hand over my business to you,

55
00:03:20.283 --> 00:03:25.070
move to a place like Hawaii, and fish every day.

56
00:03:25.413 --> 00:03:29.992
But my one-and-only grandson is a hellion.

57
00:03:30.293 --> 00:03:31.478
Oh, right.

58
00:03:31.502 --> 00:03:34.356
What do you mean, things will get troublesome?

59
00:03:34.380 --> 00:03:36.457
Right. Well...

60
00:03:37.508 --> 00:03:39.695
Due to the extreme public outrage,

61
00:03:39.719 --> 00:03:42.489
I'm afraid Mr. Park won't be
able to get a reduced sentence.

62
00:03:42.513 --> 00:03:44.491
That's what it was?

63
00:03:44.515 --> 00:03:46.035
Don't worry about that.

64
00:03:46.059 --> 00:03:49.345
I was going to get rid of him after this stint.

65
00:03:49.520 --> 00:03:51.999
Thank you for all your hard work.

66
00:03:52.023 --> 00:03:54.293
Let me know if you need anything.

67
00:03:54.317 --> 00:03:57.895
Do you want another new car?

68
00:03:58.446 --> 00:04:00.007
That reminds me.

69
00:04:00.031 --> 00:04:02.134
How's your new home? Do you like it?

70
00:04:02.158 --> 00:04:04.860
It was a very generous gift.

71
00:04:07.330 --> 00:04:09.073
Thank you so much.

72
00:04:09.290 --> 00:04:10.893
I'll work even harder.

73
00:04:10.917 --> 00:04:13.229
Forget it. Just keep up the good work.

74
00:04:13.253 --> 00:04:17.498
Do better, and you'll make me go broke.

75
00:04:18.967 --> 00:04:21.460
I'll get going then.

76
00:04:29.727 --> 00:04:31.512
Hold on.

77
00:04:31.938 --> 00:04:34.264
You seemed to have forgotten something.

78
00:04:40.238 --> 00:04:41.939
Put that down.

79
00:04:48.162 --> 00:04:50.975
People laugh when I tell them I play baseball.

80
00:04:50.999 --> 00:04:55.160
They think it's ridiculous
when I can't even run.

81
00:04:55.211 --> 00:04:57.273
But it's simple.

82
00:04:57.297 --> 00:05:00.249
If I hit a home run, I don't need to run.

83
00:05:00.300 --> 00:05:04.405
Or I can strike out.

84
00:05:04.429 --> 00:05:06.448
That's how I've lived my life.

85
00:05:06.472 --> 00:05:08.632
Hit a home run or strikeout.

86
00:05:11.978 --> 00:05:13.846
So that was the secret.

87
00:05:14.230 --> 00:05:15.541
That was how you grew...

88
00:05:15.565 --> 00:05:19.143
Yongra Construction into
Woobyeok Group so quickly.

89
00:05:19.944 --> 00:05:21.979
I'll keep that in mind.

90
00:05:22.905 --> 00:05:24.898
"Hit a home run..."

91
00:05:25.074 --> 00:05:26.817
"or strikeout."

92
00:05:32.623 --> 00:05:34.700
Gosh, that hurt.

93
00:05:34.792 --> 00:05:38.814
Gosh, you've improved a lot. You
weren't so good not too long ago.

94
00:05:38.838 --> 00:05:40.789
I practiced a lot.

95
00:05:40.923 --> 00:05:44.626
Honestly, I've always liked baseball.

96
00:05:45.344 --> 00:05:50.325
But I could neither play with
my friends nor watch them on TV.

97
00:05:50.349 --> 00:05:51.884
Why not?

98
00:05:53.519 --> 00:05:56.290
- Because I wanted to meet you.
- What?

99
00:05:56.314 --> 00:05:59.850
How would I ever have met you,
if I hadn't become a prosecutor?

100
00:05:59.942 --> 00:06:02.019
I feel the same way.

101
00:06:02.653 --> 00:06:07.649
It'd be wonderful if I had
a reliable father like you.

102
00:06:14.082 --> 00:06:15.616
All right.

103
00:06:15.708 --> 00:06:19.161
You can start addressing me as your father.

104
00:06:20.463 --> 00:06:23.317
May I really do that?

105
00:06:23.341 --> 00:06:24.359
Look at you.

106
00:06:24.383 --> 00:06:28.504
I've never seen you smile
from ear to ear before.

107
00:06:29.514 --> 00:06:34.843
Then could we go to a sauna together?

108
00:06:34.977 --> 00:06:35.996
A sauna?

109
00:06:36.020 --> 00:06:39.890
It was my lifelong dream
to scrub my father's back.

110
00:06:41.776 --> 00:06:43.477
"Father"?

111
00:06:44.654 --> 00:06:46.965
So this is how it feels.

112
00:06:46.989 --> 00:06:48.732
I love it.

113
00:06:49.784 --> 00:06:50.761
All right.

114
00:06:50.785 --> 00:06:54.822
I'll let my son scrub my back!

115
00:07:00.253 --> 00:07:02.788
"Hit a home run or a strikeout."

116
00:07:23.860 --> 00:07:25.477
Hey!

117
00:07:38.332 --> 00:07:40.227
Please identify the source,

118
00:07:40.251 --> 00:07:42.991
and look into the related articles,
organizations, and victims.

119
00:07:43.015 --> 00:07:44.758
Yes, sir.

120
00:07:47.258 --> 00:07:48.318
Sir.

121
00:07:48.342 --> 00:07:49.653
This is truly unfair!

122
00:07:49.677 --> 00:07:53.907
My son would never kill anyone!

123
00:07:53.931 --> 00:07:56.243
That wealthy chairman's grandson...

124
00:07:56.267 --> 00:07:58.704
framed my son!

125
00:07:58.728 --> 00:08:00.664
- You know that!
- Sir!

126
00:08:00.688 --> 00:08:03.250
All you need to say...

127
00:08:03.274 --> 00:08:07.796
is that my son isn't the murderer!

128
00:08:07.820 --> 00:08:09.423
- Please stop...
- Sir!

129
00:08:09.447 --> 00:08:11.633
Please, I beg you!

130
00:08:11.657 --> 00:08:14.526
- Please!
- Please let go, sir.

131
00:08:14.827 --> 00:08:16.263
- Gosh.
- Goodness.

132
00:08:16.287 --> 00:08:18.599
You impudent jerk!

133
00:08:18.623 --> 00:08:21.909
Don't you have a father?

134
00:08:33.346 --> 00:08:34.698
No, I don't.

135
00:08:34.722 --> 00:08:36.506
But...

136
00:08:37.266 --> 00:08:40.010
does having one change anything?

137
00:08:42.313 --> 00:08:47.017
You can't even help your son.
You're powerless and incompetent.

138
00:08:47.235 --> 00:08:48.894
What did you say?

139
00:08:50.488 --> 00:08:52.481
Oh, dear...

140
00:08:56.118 --> 00:08:57.179
<i><font color="#ffa07a">Jou-ri</font></i>

141
00:08:57.203 --> 00:09:00.155
Goodness...

142
00:09:00.456 --> 00:09:04.019
<i>Your call could not be completed
and will be transferred to...</i>

143
00:09:04.043 --> 00:09:06.119
He must be busy.

144
00:09:06.712 --> 00:09:10.874
Of course. You can't slack off
when you're doing important work.

145
00:09:20.351 --> 00:09:23.971
Right. The ribs.

146
00:09:38.327 --> 00:09:39.721
The seasoned vegetables,

147
00:09:39.745 --> 00:09:42.933
stir-fried glass noodles, pancakes, and...

148
00:09:42.957 --> 00:09:44.741
All done, right?

149
00:09:48.796 --> 00:09:51.164
Gosh, I can't reach it.

150
00:10:12.236 --> 00:10:16.883
How did you hurt your back?

151
00:10:16.907 --> 00:10:20.012
Those pain-relief patches only smell.

152
00:10:20.036 --> 00:10:23.322
When you've hurt your back,

153
00:10:24.206 --> 00:10:26.825
the best remedy is acupuncture.

154
00:10:26.959 --> 00:10:28.937
No, I'm okay.

155
00:10:28.961 --> 00:10:32.691
These pain-relief patches will work just fine.

156
00:10:32.715 --> 00:10:37.112
A long time ago, my uncle
fell down the stairs once.

157
00:10:37.136 --> 00:10:40.157
He thought he'd be fine just
applying pain-relief patches.

158
00:10:40.181 --> 00:10:42.424
Then he became paralyzed and bedridden.

159
00:10:42.516 --> 00:10:45.454
He developed bedsores that made his flesh rot.

160
00:10:45.478 --> 00:10:47.471
It was terrible.

161
00:10:47.688 --> 00:10:51.627
Why would you say something like that?

162
00:10:51.651 --> 00:10:54.061
I'm just saying.

163
00:10:54.570 --> 00:10:56.590
How does your stomach feel?

164
00:10:56.614 --> 00:10:58.091
Do you feel nauseated?

165
00:10:58.115 --> 00:11:02.069
Or does it feel like you've been stabbed?

166
00:11:03.871 --> 00:11:06.740
How would she know how it feels to be stabbed?

167
00:11:07.416 --> 00:11:09.034
Wouldn't she know?

168
00:11:09.085 --> 00:11:12.939
I think it's just indigestion from
tasting all the food while cooking.

169
00:11:12.963 --> 00:11:15.400
This will do the trick.

170
00:11:15.424 --> 00:11:17.167
A long time ago,

171
00:11:17.218 --> 00:11:20.655
my aunt kept downing that drink
whenever she had indigestion.

172
00:11:20.679 --> 00:11:23.715
She passed away after
getting a hole in her stomach.

173
00:11:24.141 --> 00:11:27.594
They opened her up, and
her organs had all melted.

174
00:11:29.355 --> 00:11:31.833
What's the matter with you?

175
00:11:31.857 --> 00:11:34.795
Why do you keep rambling nonsense?

176
00:11:34.819 --> 00:11:37.422
I'm just saying.

177
00:11:37.446 --> 00:11:39.606
Don't worry.

178
00:11:41.742 --> 00:11:43.652
My baby.

179
00:11:45.413 --> 00:11:46.390
Right.

180
00:11:46.414 --> 00:11:49.559
I'm thinking of naming our puppy Kang-ho.

181
00:11:49.583 --> 00:11:50.602
What?

182
00:11:50.626 --> 00:11:52.479
Why that name?

183
00:11:52.503 --> 00:11:54.356
If you think about it,

184
00:11:54.380 --> 00:11:57.150
everyone with that name seems to prosper.

185
00:11:57.174 --> 00:12:00.862
There's Song Kang-ho and there's Choi Kang-ho.

186
00:12:00.886 --> 00:12:03.281
I want our puppy to prosper too.

187
00:12:03.305 --> 00:12:08.760
A prosperous dog will still be
a dog. It won't turn into a tiger.

188
00:12:09.311 --> 00:12:11.164
A tiger?

189
00:12:11.188 --> 00:12:12.582
Oh, my.

190
00:12:12.606 --> 00:12:14.918
Let's name our dog Tiger.

191
00:12:14.942 --> 00:12:17.712
Then it'll become a tiger, won't it?

192
00:12:17.736 --> 00:12:21.258
Tiger, roar for me.

193
00:12:21.282 --> 00:12:24.344
Roar for me.

194
00:12:24.368 --> 00:12:26.361
Don't mind her.

195
00:12:27.580 --> 00:12:31.992
So tell me. How's our prosecutor doing?

196
00:12:32.626 --> 00:12:38.623
He's never visited ever since moving to Seoul.

197
00:12:39.175 --> 00:12:42.863
He actually called in the
afternoon and said he'd visit.

198
00:12:42.887 --> 00:12:45.031
But I dissuaded him.

199
00:12:45.055 --> 00:12:47.617
He has trials lined up back-to-back,

200
00:12:47.641 --> 00:12:50.662
so I told him to just rest on the weekend.

201
00:12:50.686 --> 00:12:51.663
I see.

202
00:12:51.687 --> 00:12:54.166
I tracked down the IP address of the posts...

203
00:12:54.190 --> 00:12:56.251
that were posted on the media sites.

204
00:12:56.275 --> 00:12:58.712
This is footage from an
internet café in Sangdo-dong.

205
00:12:58.736 --> 00:13:03.273
I believe they're exposing Woobyeok
Group's corruption to the press.

206
00:13:08.204 --> 00:13:09.455
<i><font color="#ffa07a">Ha-young</font></i>

207
00:13:12.458 --> 00:13:14.144
Did he reject your call again?

208
00:13:14.168 --> 00:13:15.994
Yes.

209
00:13:17.296 --> 00:13:18.732
Should I call one more time?

210
00:13:18.756 --> 00:13:20.582
Hey.

211
00:13:21.550 --> 00:13:24.211
Forget it. Just end it.

212
00:13:24.261 --> 00:13:28.340
I get that he's busy, but
he's been ignoring you for days.

213
00:13:28.891 --> 00:13:31.995
I'm pretty sure he's seeing someone else.

214
00:13:32.019 --> 00:13:33.803
Hey...

215
00:13:35.523 --> 00:13:37.501
Oh, no. I'm sorry.

216
00:13:37.525 --> 00:13:38.960
Hey, are you okay?

217
00:13:38.984 --> 00:13:41.019
- Here...
- Oh, no.

218
00:13:42.029 --> 00:13:43.381
Goodness, what's wrong?

219
00:13:43.405 --> 00:13:44.883
My goodness!

220
00:13:44.907 --> 00:13:46.801
Oh, dear. I'm sorry.

221
00:13:46.825 --> 00:13:48.094
I'm so sorry.

222
00:13:48.118 --> 00:13:50.138
Hurry up and apologize.

223
00:13:50.162 --> 00:13:51.640
I'm so sorry.

224
00:13:51.664 --> 00:13:54.434
You don't know what I do?

225
00:13:54.458 --> 00:13:55.393
Sorry?

226
00:13:55.417 --> 00:13:57.953
I'm a ballerina.

227
00:13:58.003 --> 00:14:01.915
Is that the best apology
after almost cutting off my toe?

228
00:14:02.341 --> 00:14:04.042
Right.

229
00:14:06.971 --> 00:14:09.089
I'm really sorry.

230
00:14:10.683 --> 00:14:12.801
This is so annoying.

231
00:14:13.811 --> 00:14:15.345
Let's go.

232
00:14:20.526 --> 00:14:22.102
I'm sorry.

233
00:14:24.196 --> 00:14:25.882
Are you okay?

234
00:14:25.906 --> 00:14:27.691
Wait.

235
00:14:33.080 --> 00:14:35.824
It's your turn now.

236
00:14:36.877 --> 00:14:37.853
What?

237
00:14:37.877 --> 00:14:40.647
Please apologize for kicking me.

238
00:14:40.671 --> 00:14:42.190
Mi-joo, what's with you?

239
00:14:42.214 --> 00:14:45.301
If you're that sensitive about your
feet, you shouldn't have come here.

240
00:14:45.325 --> 00:14:47.696
- Have you gone crazy?
- No, ma'am.

241
00:14:47.720 --> 00:14:49.739
Not yet.

242
00:14:49.763 --> 00:14:53.300
But I'll go crazy if you don't apologize.

243
00:15:05.112 --> 00:15:07.105
I won't apologize.

244
00:15:07.990 --> 00:15:09.509
There.

245
00:15:09.533 --> 00:15:11.359
What'll you do now?

246
00:15:12.411 --> 00:15:14.097
What?

247
00:15:14.121 --> 00:15:15.905
What?

248
00:15:17.166 --> 00:15:19.159
I see.

249
00:15:19.501 --> 00:15:22.912
In that case, it can't be helped.

250
00:15:31.472 --> 00:15:33.423
She didn't hit you.

251
00:15:37.519 --> 00:15:40.138
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

252
00:15:45.569 --> 00:15:47.547
The last time I felt this satisfied...

253
00:15:47.571 --> 00:15:50.216
was when I got my first Brazilian waxing.

254
00:15:50.240 --> 00:15:52.469
She shouldn't have provoked me.

255
00:15:52.493 --> 00:15:54.986
But what are you going to do now?

256
00:15:56.372 --> 00:15:58.516
- I won't vote for him.
- What do you mean?

257
00:15:58.540 --> 00:15:59.476
Vote for who?

258
00:15:59.500 --> 00:16:02.062
Her dad will be running for President.

259
00:16:02.086 --> 00:16:04.037
He'll never get my vote.

260
00:16:04.713 --> 00:16:08.458
Sure. That's the worst you could do.

261
00:16:15.391 --> 00:16:18.259
I'm going to open a small salon...

262
00:16:18.352 --> 00:16:20.497
with the money I've saved up.

263
00:16:20.521 --> 00:16:22.916
- A salon?
- Yes.

264
00:16:22.940 --> 00:16:27.128
I wanted to save up for two more
years and open up a big one in Seoul.

265
00:16:27.152 --> 00:16:29.673
But I should look outside
the city or a shop-in-shop.

266
00:16:29.697 --> 00:16:31.341
- Mi-joo.
- Yes?

267
00:16:31.365 --> 00:16:33.301
Me too. I want in.

268
00:16:33.325 --> 00:16:35.220
- I'll chip in.
- Seriously?

269
00:16:35.244 --> 00:16:38.682
I'll chip in so we can look for a
place on the outskirts of Seoul.

270
00:16:38.706 --> 00:16:40.365
What do you say?

271
00:16:40.833 --> 00:16:44.771
Sun-young, I'd love that!

272
00:16:44.795 --> 00:16:46.147
- Really?
- Yes!

273
00:16:46.171 --> 00:16:47.607
Okay!

274
00:16:47.631 --> 00:16:49.943
Then you can be the owner.

275
00:16:49.967 --> 00:16:52.862
- What?
- I'll be the CEO.

276
00:16:52.886 --> 00:16:54.030
What?

277
00:16:54.054 --> 00:16:56.241
That's ridiculous.

278
00:16:56.265 --> 00:16:58.410
- All right then.
- Okay.

279
00:16:58.434 --> 00:16:59.995
I look forward to it, ma'am.

280
00:17:00.019 --> 00:17:01.955
I'll do my best, Ms. CEO.

281
00:17:01.979 --> 00:17:03.707
- Let me.
- You can speak casually.

282
00:17:03.731 --> 00:17:04.731
<i><font color="#ffa07a">Mom</font></i>

283
00:17:05.733 --> 00:17:07.627
Please excuse me for a minute, Ms. CEO.

284
00:17:07.651 --> 00:17:10.186
- Sure, take the call.
- Thank you.

285
00:17:12.197 --> 00:17:14.023
Hi, Mom.

286
00:17:14.408 --> 00:17:15.927
<i>I'm not your mom.</i>

287
00:17:15.951 --> 00:17:19.988
Who told you you could use Grandma's phone?

288
00:17:20.247 --> 00:17:23.825
<i>Grandma is dead.</i>

289
00:17:25.044 --> 00:17:27.647
What? What are you saying?

290
00:17:27.671 --> 00:17:28.982
Why is she dead?

291
00:17:29.006 --> 00:17:31.151
<i>She ran out.</i>

292
00:17:31.175 --> 00:17:32.318
"Ran out"?

293
00:17:32.342 --> 00:17:33.945
Yes.

294
00:17:33.969 --> 00:17:35.572
Goodness.

295
00:17:35.596 --> 00:17:37.866
She ran out of cards,

296
00:17:37.890 --> 00:17:41.745
so she lost the match and all her money.

297
00:17:41.769 --> 00:17:44.497
She's as good as dead for this round.

298
00:17:44.521 --> 00:17:45.749
Hey!

299
00:17:45.773 --> 00:17:47.625
You startled me!

300
00:17:47.649 --> 00:17:50.128
- Who's that?
- Mom.

301
00:17:50.152 --> 00:17:51.671
Mom?

302
00:17:51.695 --> 00:17:52.922
Do you mean...

303
00:17:52.946 --> 00:17:54.090
Mi-joo?

304
00:17:54.114 --> 00:17:56.885
Your youngest daughter who's in the U.S.?

305
00:17:56.909 --> 00:17:58.261
Give that to me.

306
00:17:58.285 --> 00:17:59.304
Hello?

307
00:17:59.328 --> 00:18:02.766
Mom, didn't I tell you not to
play cards with the kids around?

308
00:18:02.790 --> 00:18:03.725
<i>What?</i>

309
00:18:03.749 --> 00:18:06.144
You want to send me money?

310
00:18:06.168 --> 00:18:10.231
Gosh, you don't need to send
me your hard-earned money.

311
00:18:10.255 --> 00:18:14.778
Gosh, seems Mi-joo is trying
to send you money. How lucky.

312
00:18:14.802 --> 00:18:16.946
Her daughter sends her money,

313
00:18:16.970 --> 00:18:20.992
while we work like dogs to buy
food for our incarcerated son.

314
00:18:21.016 --> 00:18:23.578
Why is my life so miserable?

315
00:18:23.602 --> 00:18:25.080
<i>I'm not sending you any money.</i>

316
00:18:25.104 --> 00:18:27.713
- Would you like me to read your fortune?
- <i>And I won't be...</i>

317
00:18:27.737 --> 00:18:29.751
<i>sending you any money for the time being.</i>

318
00:18:29.775 --> 00:18:31.169
I'm opening a nail salon.

319
00:18:31.193 --> 00:18:32.128
What?

320
00:18:32.152 --> 00:18:34.896
Your husband is opening a nail salon for you?

321
00:18:34.988 --> 00:18:37.133
Goodness. That's great.

322
00:18:37.157 --> 00:18:38.593
What?

323
00:18:38.617 --> 00:18:40.053
Good job.

324
00:18:40.077 --> 00:18:41.846
"Nail"? What's a "nail salon"?

325
00:18:41.870 --> 00:18:43.515
Why did you call?

326
00:18:43.539 --> 00:18:45.100
Ye-jin is the one who called.

327
00:18:45.124 --> 00:18:48.144
I told you not to give them your phone.

328
00:18:48.168 --> 00:18:50.563
Watching videos will worsen their eyesight.

329
00:18:50.587 --> 00:18:53.149
If you're that concerned,
you can raise them instead.

330
00:18:53.173 --> 00:18:56.653
Right. What happened to that jerk?

331
00:18:56.677 --> 00:18:58.488
What jerk?

332
00:18:58.512 --> 00:19:00.949
The father of your children!

333
00:19:00.973 --> 00:19:02.590
Goodness.

334
00:19:04.810 --> 00:19:06.845
Have you found him?

335
00:19:06.937 --> 00:19:09.582
Didn't we agree not to talk about that anymore?

336
00:19:09.606 --> 00:19:12.418
And I chose not to look for him.

337
00:19:12.442 --> 00:19:13.878
It's over between us.

338
00:19:13.902 --> 00:19:16.172
<i>What are you talking about?</i>

339
00:19:16.196 --> 00:19:19.134
What will you say to the people here?

340
00:19:19.158 --> 00:19:22.053
What will you tell your kids?

341
00:19:22.077 --> 00:19:25.098
They think you're working hard in the U.S...

342
00:19:25.122 --> 00:19:26.683
and will send for them.

343
00:19:26.707 --> 00:19:29.394
So why did you have to lie to them?

344
00:19:29.418 --> 00:19:32.063
Whatever. Just say I got divorced.

345
00:19:32.087 --> 00:19:34.957
You want me to tell them that you,
alongside Jin-joo and Seon-joo,

346
00:19:34.981 --> 00:19:36.526
are divorced too?

347
00:19:36.550 --> 00:19:39.070
Is our family cursed or something?

348
00:19:39.094 --> 00:19:43.116
Goodness. Do you know how embarrassing it is?

349
00:19:43.140 --> 00:19:45.743
<i>You're the one who started it all.</i>

350
00:19:45.767 --> 00:19:47.495
I never got a divorce.

351
00:19:47.519 --> 00:19:49.455
But he left you for another woman.

352
00:19:49.479 --> 00:19:51.890
At least I was married when I had kids!

353
00:19:52.191 --> 00:19:53.975
- Hang up!
- Hang up!

354
00:19:56.236 --> 00:19:57.979
This rotten brat.

355
00:19:58.280 --> 00:20:01.885
Why does her life have to
be so miserable like mine?

356
00:20:01.909 --> 00:20:03.860
Goodness, you startled me.

357
00:20:04.077 --> 00:20:06.487
Who had kids out of wedlock?

358
00:20:06.747 --> 00:20:09.032
We were talking about a drama.

359
00:20:12.920 --> 00:20:15.997
Sam-sik will be released soon, right?

360
00:20:16.548 --> 00:20:17.692
What should I do?

361
00:20:17.716 --> 00:20:21.487
Should we carry out a
ritual when he's released?

362
00:20:21.511 --> 00:20:23.114
Just pack up and leave.

363
00:20:23.138 --> 00:20:25.575
There's absolutely no
ritual that could fix this.

364
00:20:25.599 --> 00:20:28.828
There's no deity who can change his fate.

365
00:20:28.852 --> 00:20:30.663
So just leave.

366
00:20:30.687 --> 00:20:32.373
- Let me.
- It's okay.

367
00:20:32.397 --> 00:20:34.125
Look who's here!

368
00:20:34.149 --> 00:20:37.629
It's the woman who's been
blessed with everything.

369
00:20:37.653 --> 00:20:41.007
Prosecutor Choi's mother is here!

370
00:20:41.031 --> 00:20:42.300
- Goodness.
- Hello.

371
00:20:42.324 --> 00:20:44.385
- Gosh, you didn't have to.
- Hello.

372
00:20:44.409 --> 00:20:46.512
- Come on in.
- It's okay.

373
00:20:46.536 --> 00:20:48.765
I have to leave for Seoul.

374
00:20:48.789 --> 00:20:51.601
I made <i>geotjeori</i> and a few side dishes. Enjoy.

375
00:20:51.625 --> 00:20:55.188
- So that's why you're all dolled up.
- Goodness.

376
00:20:55.212 --> 00:20:57.649
- You're going to see your son.
- Yes.

377
00:20:57.673 --> 00:20:59.275
What's wrong with your arm?

378
00:20:59.299 --> 00:21:02.001
You seemed to be limping too.

379
00:21:02.177 --> 00:21:05.490
I fell in the kitchen yesterday, but I'm okay.

380
00:21:05.514 --> 00:21:07.533
You're such a doting mother.

381
00:21:07.557 --> 00:21:09.827
A successful prosecutor like him...

382
00:21:09.851 --> 00:21:13.221
must have good and expensive food all the time.

383
00:21:13.313 --> 00:21:14.749
Still, it's his birthday.

384
00:21:14.773 --> 00:21:18.294
- Is it? Then you should go.
- Yes.

385
00:21:18.318 --> 00:21:20.004
- Have a safe trip.
- Okay.

386
00:21:20.028 --> 00:21:22.423
Please enjoy the food.

387
00:21:22.447 --> 00:21:24.175
Ye-jin and Seo-jin, eat lots.

388
00:21:24.199 --> 00:21:26.052
- Okay, goodbye.
- Okay, goodbye.

389
00:21:26.076 --> 00:21:27.804
- Goodbye.
- Have a safe trip.

390
00:21:27.828 --> 00:21:29.639
- Bye.
- Gosh.

391
00:21:29.663 --> 00:21:32.225
How can I enjoy her food
when it looks like that?

392
00:21:32.249 --> 00:21:34.283
It's tasty.

393
00:21:34.334 --> 00:21:35.478
Try some.

394
00:21:35.502 --> 00:21:37.078
Here.

395
00:21:37.170 --> 00:21:38.189
I'm on a diet.

396
00:21:38.213 --> 00:21:39.998
Hold on.

397
00:21:41.091 --> 00:21:46.254
If it's Kang-ho's birthday,
then it's Mi-joo's birthday too.

398
00:21:46.763 --> 00:21:48.548
You're right.

399
00:21:50.100 --> 00:21:51.661
Goodness.

400
00:21:51.685 --> 00:21:55.930
You brat. You should've told
me it's your birthday today!

401
00:21:56.398 --> 00:21:58.084
What's your bank account number?

402
00:21:58.108 --> 00:22:01.629
<i>So which building and unit is it?</i>

403
00:22:01.653 --> 00:22:04.048
I'm calling him right now.

404
00:22:04.072 --> 00:22:06.149
Why isn't he picking up?

405
00:22:06.992 --> 00:22:09.095
Sir, it's me.

406
00:22:09.119 --> 00:22:13.698
I'm at the address you sent me.
But which building and unit is it?

407
00:22:15.001 --> 00:22:15.977
Sorry?

408
00:22:16.001 --> 00:22:17.645
- I'm sorry.
- Okay.

409
00:22:17.669 --> 00:22:20.023
What are you doing?

410
00:22:20.047 --> 00:22:22.025
Pull up over there.

411
00:22:22.049 --> 00:22:23.985
- Pull up.
- Okay.

412
00:22:24.009 --> 00:22:25.960
One minute please.

413
00:22:31.516 --> 00:22:34.969
<i>You have a call from the lobby.</i>

414
00:22:36.688 --> 00:22:37.665
Yes?

415
00:22:37.689 --> 00:22:41.044
<i>Hello, sir. This is the security office.</i>

416
00:22:41.068 --> 00:22:44.005
<i>Your mother is here.</i>

417
00:22:44.029 --> 00:22:45.089
Tell her I'm not home.

418
00:22:45.113 --> 00:22:46.049
Sorry?

419
00:22:46.073 --> 00:22:48.941
Tell her you're not home?

420
00:22:51.912 --> 00:22:55.323
But she brought a bunch of food.

421
00:22:55.916 --> 00:22:58.242
Hello?

422
00:23:02.297 --> 00:23:05.750
You see, Mr. Choi is...

423
00:23:06.051 --> 00:23:09.295
What is it? He's not home yet?

424
00:23:09.596 --> 00:23:12.784
I understand. He's one of the
top prosecutors in this country.

425
00:23:12.808 --> 00:23:14.660
Of course he's busy.

426
00:23:14.684 --> 00:23:17.345
I should've called in advance.

427
00:23:17.480 --> 00:23:18.456
In that case,

428
00:23:18.480 --> 00:23:23.100
could you please give him these for me?

429
00:23:23.443 --> 00:23:25.436
Goodness.

430
00:23:25.779 --> 00:23:27.855
- Thank you.
- No problem.

431
00:23:29.574 --> 00:23:31.317
Sir.

432
00:23:31.827 --> 00:23:33.137
Do you see him at times?

433
00:23:33.161 --> 00:23:35.848
Yes, every now and then.

434
00:23:35.872 --> 00:23:38.351
How is he? Does he look okay?

435
00:23:38.375 --> 00:23:40.019
Does he look healthy?

436
00:23:40.043 --> 00:23:43.981
Yes. He's such a handsome man...

437
00:23:44.005 --> 00:23:46.999
who takes great care of himself.

438
00:23:47.968 --> 00:23:52.031
Has he ever gotten drunk and looked depressed?

439
00:23:52.055 --> 00:23:55.383
No, I don't think so.

440
00:23:56.393 --> 00:23:58.246
That's good. Goodbye.

441
00:23:58.270 --> 00:23:59.929
Goodbye.

442
00:24:00.105 --> 00:24:01.207
One minute.

443
00:24:01.231 --> 00:24:02.765
Sorry?

444
00:24:05.735 --> 00:24:07.588
If anything seems off,

445
00:24:07.612 --> 00:24:10.591
please give me a call.

446
00:24:10.615 --> 00:24:12.135
- Okay.
- Thank you.

447
00:24:12.159 --> 00:24:15.361
- No problem.
- Goodbye.

448
00:24:18.748 --> 00:24:20.685
I wonder if she's eaten.

449
00:24:20.709 --> 00:24:22.827
She seems to be in pain.

450
00:24:25.213 --> 00:24:27.275
So what if he's a prosecutor?

451
00:24:27.299 --> 00:24:29.208
He's so impudent.

452
00:24:34.681 --> 00:24:36.016
<i><font color="#ffff00">Choco Pie</font></i>

453
00:24:44.232 --> 00:24:46.601
He's just busy. That's all.

454
00:24:59.289 --> 00:25:01.100
<i>With a 33% approval rate,</i>

455
00:25:01.124 --> 00:25:03.081
<i>Assemblyman Oh Tae-soo defeated Park Gil-ung,</i>

456
00:25:03.105 --> 00:25:05.917
<i>former chairman of Bareun Hanguk Party
and a leading candidate of the opposing camp,</i>

457
00:25:05.941 --> 00:25:08.915
<i>and established himself as
the next presidential candidate.</i>

458
00:25:09.090 --> 00:25:11.960
<i>Assemblyman Oh, who led the ruling
party to a landslide victory...</i>

459
00:25:11.984 --> 00:25:14.614
<i>as former committee chairman
of the Jeilmirae Party,</i>

460
00:25:14.638 --> 00:25:16.866
<i>emerged as a leading presidential candidate...</i>

461
00:25:16.890 --> 00:25:18.868
<i>through his election and the party's victory.</i>

462
00:25:18.892 --> 00:25:20.745
<i><font color="#ffff00">Become a Passionate Judicial Officer</font></i>

463
00:25:20.769 --> 00:25:24.096
Do you know why people bad-mouth
judicial officers of this country?

464
00:25:24.272 --> 00:25:26.807
Because all they know is to study.

465
00:25:26.983 --> 00:25:30.922
But studying is merely a talent,

466
00:25:30.946 --> 00:25:32.798
just like singing or drawing.

467
00:25:32.822 --> 00:25:35.676
It doesn't make you superior to others.

468
00:25:35.700 --> 00:25:40.598
Perhaps those who only know how
to study could be the most inferior.

469
00:25:40.622 --> 00:25:42.198
Let's be honest.

470
00:25:42.249 --> 00:25:43.851
You don't have friends.

471
00:25:43.875 --> 00:25:45.701
Aren't you all outcasts?

472
00:25:47.087 --> 00:25:49.857
But those idiots act like
being a prosecutor or a judge...

473
00:25:49.881 --> 00:25:54.528
is the most powerful right a human could have.

474
00:25:54.552 --> 00:25:56.447
That's why people bash them.

475
00:25:56.471 --> 00:26:00.451
A true judicial officer must
be able to both think and feel.

476
00:26:00.475 --> 00:26:05.373
Those with no friends or
empathy toward others...

477
00:26:05.397 --> 00:26:08.209
studied hard to prosecute, defend,

478
00:26:08.233 --> 00:26:09.794
and judge others?

479
00:26:09.818 --> 00:26:12.713
No wonder the world has turned out this way.

480
00:26:12.737 --> 00:26:16.774
No wonder only the weak
and the innocent are victimized.

481
00:26:17.284 --> 00:26:20.054
Let me ask you future
judicial officers for a favor,

482
00:26:20.078 --> 00:26:22.723
as an old, former judicial officer.

483
00:26:22.747 --> 00:26:26.435
We've been overworking
our brains for far too long.

484
00:26:26.459 --> 00:26:29.438
So let's stop doing that,

485
00:26:29.462 --> 00:26:33.541
and use our passionate
hearts to guide us instead.

486
00:26:33.842 --> 00:26:35.302
{\an8}<i><font color="#ffa07a">Oh Tae-soo</font></i>

487
00:26:36.845 --> 00:26:40.381
That's enough. Get going now.

488
00:26:41.057 --> 00:26:44.203
Tae-soo, this is Choi Kang-ho.

489
00:26:44.227 --> 00:26:46.497
He entered the institute
at the top of his class.

490
00:26:46.521 --> 00:26:49.625
He's a talent who's always
placed first in his class.

491
00:26:49.649 --> 00:26:51.684
Really?

492
00:26:52.652 --> 00:26:54.463
- Are we alumni?
- Yes.

493
00:26:54.487 --> 00:26:56.173
It's an honor to meet you, sir.

494
00:26:56.197 --> 00:27:00.344
With your grades, it'll only be a
matter of time until you become a judge.

495
00:27:00.368 --> 00:27:03.014
I actually aspire to become a prosecutor.

496
00:27:03.038 --> 00:27:05.391
You're his role model.

497
00:27:05.415 --> 00:27:09.478
He's an avid fan of yours who's memorized...

498
00:27:09.502 --> 00:27:11.314
all your books and theses.

499
00:27:11.338 --> 00:27:12.997
Really?

500
00:27:13.131 --> 00:27:14.191
I'm honored.

501
00:27:14.215 --> 00:27:16.417
Not at all.

502
00:27:18.303 --> 00:27:19.920
Goodbye, sir.

503
00:27:27.812 --> 00:27:31.000
Have we met before?

504
00:27:31.024 --> 00:27:32.641
You look familiar.

505
00:27:34.235 --> 00:27:37.131
No, sir. We've never met.

506
00:27:37.155 --> 00:27:38.382
But...

507
00:27:38.406 --> 00:27:39.925
Actually,

508
00:27:39.949 --> 00:27:43.027
- you've met my father...
- Dad.

509
00:27:43.995 --> 00:27:45.556
We're late. Let's go.

510
00:27:45.580 --> 00:27:47.433
Okay.

511
00:27:47.457 --> 00:27:48.851
I need to go.

512
00:27:48.875 --> 00:27:50.978
See you next time.

513
00:27:51.002 --> 00:27:53.788
Yes, sir. I'll make sure we meet again.

514
00:27:58.635 --> 00:28:00.878
She's so pretty.

515
00:28:00.970 --> 00:28:02.838
You're so pretty.

516
00:28:26.955 --> 00:28:29.949
I'm not interested, so get lost.

517
00:28:31.751 --> 00:28:34.411
You'll be interested soon.

518
00:28:41.803 --> 00:28:43.489
Have you gone insane?

519
00:28:43.513 --> 00:28:45.908
I didn't do any drugs.

520
00:28:45.932 --> 00:28:48.259
Do you have proof?

521
00:28:48.685 --> 00:28:51.429
This is driving me crazy.

522
00:28:56.651 --> 00:28:58.713
You're going to regret this.

523
00:28:58.737 --> 00:29:00.381
I won't let this slide.

524
00:29:00.405 --> 00:29:02.508
I'll get you all fired.

525
00:29:02.532 --> 00:29:04.343
You can take your time with that.

526
00:29:04.367 --> 00:29:06.277
What's this?

527
00:29:11.666 --> 00:29:12.893
It's just medicine.

528
00:29:12.917 --> 00:29:15.828
Exactly. What kind of medicine?

529
00:29:18.173 --> 00:29:19.915
Please answer.

530
00:29:20.717 --> 00:29:22.710
It's for my panic disorder.

531
00:29:22.844 --> 00:29:24.196
You have panic disorder?

532
00:29:24.220 --> 00:29:26.505
It's not serious.

533
00:29:29.309 --> 00:29:31.245
Wait! What are you doing?

534
00:29:31.269 --> 00:29:32.872
Hey! What are you doing?

535
00:29:32.896 --> 00:29:34.039
- Hey!
- Stay still.

536
00:29:34.063 --> 00:29:35.249
- You lunatic!
- Stay still.

537
00:29:35.273 --> 00:29:36.667
Wait! No!

538
00:29:36.691 --> 00:29:39.462
Do you know how expensive that is?

539
00:29:39.486 --> 00:29:41.255
No! That's a limited-edition!

540
00:29:41.279 --> 00:29:43.106
- They don't sell it anymore.
- Stay still!

541
00:29:43.130 --> 00:29:44.842
- Please!
- The urinalysis came out.

542
00:29:44.866 --> 00:29:46.942
They all tested negative.

543
00:29:57.003 --> 00:30:00.274
I believe there was a mistake
in the report we received.

544
00:30:00.298 --> 00:30:01.317
I'm sorry.

545
00:30:01.341 --> 00:30:02.318
You're sorry?

546
00:30:02.342 --> 00:30:04.043
Are you?

547
00:30:05.804 --> 00:30:07.865
That's all you can say after ruining this?

548
00:30:07.889 --> 00:30:09.965
I'll compensate for that.

549
00:30:12.685 --> 00:30:16.430
My dad was a former prosecutor
so I know how much you make.

550
00:30:18.525 --> 00:30:19.710
Don't be ridiculous.

551
00:30:19.734 --> 00:30:23.687
This is more expensive than your life.

552
00:30:28.243 --> 00:30:30.110
Let's go.

553
00:30:32.205 --> 00:30:34.156
Will it be okay?

554
00:30:35.208 --> 00:30:37.394
It hurts, but I'm okay.

555
00:30:37.418 --> 00:30:39.230
No, I'm talking about us.

556
00:30:39.254 --> 00:30:43.943
It says here that she's the
daughter of Assemblyman Oh Tae-soo,

557
00:30:43.967 --> 00:30:46.320
a former chief prosecutor.

558
00:30:46.344 --> 00:30:47.920
What?

559
00:30:49.097 --> 00:30:51.924
How may we help you?

560
00:30:56.729 --> 00:30:58.541
I shouldn't have hit you.

561
00:30:58.565 --> 00:30:59.875
That's okay.

562
00:30:59.899 --> 00:31:03.769
It's all right. He deserved it.

563
00:31:04.362 --> 00:31:09.066
But by any chance, will
my time here be recorded?

564
00:31:09.117 --> 00:31:11.735
You won't call my parents, will you?

565
00:31:13.788 --> 00:31:17.157
It was my first time clubbing.

566
00:31:20.295 --> 00:31:22.121
Make that the second or third.

567
00:31:22.297 --> 00:31:24.441
As for my panic disorder,

568
00:31:24.465 --> 00:31:25.943
it's really not that bad.

569
00:31:25.967 --> 00:31:27.611
I just...

570
00:31:27.635 --> 00:31:29.113
have trouble sleeping.

571
00:31:29.137 --> 00:31:32.089
I'm just taking it to prevent it from worsening.

572
00:31:32.932 --> 00:31:35.634
So let's pretend today never happened.

573
00:31:36.477 --> 00:31:38.664
You don't need to compensate for the bag either.

574
00:31:38.688 --> 00:31:41.292
I'm sick of it, so I was
going to throw it away anyway.

575
00:31:41.316 --> 00:31:44.560
Then I'll assume you understand.

576
00:31:44.819 --> 00:31:45.921
I'll go now.

577
00:31:45.945 --> 00:31:47.688
Goodbye.

578
