00:32:16.392 --> 00:32:18.203
♫ <i>don't fight</i> ♫

586
00:32:18.227 --> 00:32:22.166
♫ <i>Let's love each other</i> ♫

587
00:32:22.190 --> 00:32:25.753
♫ <i>Pinky promise</i> ♫

588
00:32:25.777 --> 00:32:30.648
♫ <i>Promise me</i> ♫

589
00:32:32.408 --> 00:32:35.569
Come here. Hurry up.

590
00:32:37.997 --> 00:32:39.850
Are you crazy?

591
00:32:39.874 --> 00:32:42.409
How could you come here?

592
00:32:44.212 --> 00:32:46.413
We agreed to forget about it.

593
00:32:46.798 --> 00:32:48.233
I got you a new bag.

594
00:32:48.257 --> 00:32:49.958
What?

595
00:32:52.303 --> 00:32:53.948
What is this?

596
00:32:53.972 --> 00:32:57.466
You actually got a new one?
It was a limited-edition.

597
00:32:59.936 --> 00:33:01.497
What?

598
00:33:01.521 --> 00:33:03.555
Are you serious?

599
00:33:04.190 --> 00:33:06.016
No way.

600
00:33:06.776 --> 00:33:08.560
What's this?

601
00:33:08.695 --> 00:33:11.438
Where's the bag? This is just a dust bag...

602
00:33:12.949 --> 00:33:14.525
Sir.

603
00:33:14.701 --> 00:33:18.195
You do know how well-respected
your father is, right?

604
00:33:18.788 --> 00:33:23.310
The people trust and support
him due to his humility.

605
00:33:23.334 --> 00:33:25.938
So should you carry such an expensive bag,

606
00:33:25.962 --> 00:33:29.164
and go clubbing with your wealthy friends?

607
00:33:29.215 --> 00:33:32.903
Stop tainting his reputation, and carry that.

608
00:33:32.927 --> 00:33:35.879
Who are you to tell me what to do?

609
00:33:40.518 --> 00:33:42.344
What is this?

610
00:33:46.315 --> 00:33:49.351
Jujubes are said to be natural tranquilizers.

611
00:33:49.444 --> 00:33:51.630
You said your symptoms weren't severe,

612
00:33:51.654 --> 00:33:53.716
so don't take any medication.

613
00:33:53.740 --> 00:33:56.400
Just have some jujube tea before bed.

614
00:33:57.785 --> 00:34:01.864
I went to the marketplace in the morning
to get them, so don't throw them away.

615
00:34:05.168 --> 00:34:06.869
What the...?

616
00:34:14.510 --> 00:34:16.086
Dad.

617
00:34:18.181 --> 00:34:21.341
- Happy birthday.
- Thanks.

618
00:34:21.476 --> 00:34:23.260
I'm glad my daughter...

619
00:34:29.233 --> 00:34:30.768
Who is he?

620
00:34:31.861 --> 00:34:34.855
Hello, I'm Choi Kang-ho.

621
00:34:36.657 --> 00:34:38.859
You must be surprised.

622
00:34:38.910 --> 00:34:41.069
He's your birthday gift.

623
00:34:41.120 --> 00:34:42.264
Your future son-in-law.

624
00:34:42.288 --> 00:34:43.906
What?

625
00:34:57.220 --> 00:34:58.822
You brat.

626
00:34:58.846 --> 00:35:02.424
What took you so long to
introduce such a fine, young man?

627
00:35:04.352 --> 00:35:07.262
All right. Have a seat.

628
00:35:08.398 --> 00:35:09.374
{\an8}That's right.

629
00:35:09.398 --> 00:35:11.725
{\an8}Judicial Research and Training Institute.

630
00:35:11.943 --> 00:35:14.311
No wonder you seemed familiar.

631
00:35:15.988 --> 00:35:18.050
It must've been hard...

632
00:35:18.074 --> 00:35:20.886
to grow up without a father.

633
00:35:20.910 --> 00:35:24.681
But he grew up so well and
became a competent prosecutor.

634
00:35:24.705 --> 00:35:26.433
Even I'm proud of you.

635
00:35:26.457 --> 00:35:29.520
I still have a long way to go.
I hope to learn from you.

636
00:35:29.544 --> 00:35:30.562
All right.

637
00:35:30.586 --> 00:35:32.606
I hope we get along.

638
00:35:32.630 --> 00:35:34.456
Yes, sir.

639
00:35:35.299 --> 00:35:37.069
It's getting late.

640
00:35:37.093 --> 00:35:40.072
How about you ladies give us some privacy?

641
00:35:40.096 --> 00:35:41.740
Why?

642
00:35:41.764 --> 00:35:43.617
What will you talk about without us?

643
00:35:43.641 --> 00:35:47.246
Men have things to talk about among themselves.

644
00:35:47.270 --> 00:35:48.872
- Right?
- Yes, you're right.

645
00:35:48.896 --> 00:35:50.681
Exactly.

646
00:35:51.899 --> 00:35:53.919
Don't make him drink too much.

647
00:35:53.943 --> 00:35:56.547
- It's okay.
- Look at that.

648
00:35:56.571 --> 00:35:58.882
A daughter will always put her boyfriend first.

649
00:35:58.906 --> 00:36:01.066
Honey, take her.

650
00:36:01.159 --> 00:36:04.069
- Call me when you get home.
- I will.

651
00:36:04.453 --> 00:36:05.722
See you later, ma'am.

652
00:36:05.746 --> 00:36:07.099
Bye, Dad.

653
00:36:07.123 --> 00:36:08.657
Bye.

654
00:36:25.141 --> 00:36:27.092
So what will it be?

655
00:36:27.310 --> 00:36:28.287
Sorry?

656
00:36:28.311 --> 00:36:30.721
The reason for your breakup.

657
00:36:30.771 --> 00:36:32.791
Another woman?

658
00:36:32.815 --> 00:36:36.101
Or do you want to be sent abroad for work?

659
00:36:36.235 --> 00:36:39.631
Or I could make you a corrupt
prosecutor and send you to prison.

660
00:36:39.655 --> 00:36:42.274
I can't suddenly kill you off.

661
00:36:48.164 --> 00:36:50.741
You reek of something.

662
00:36:50.833 --> 00:36:53.243
Ever since we first met.

663
00:36:53.377 --> 00:36:55.147
What could it be?

664
00:36:55.171 --> 00:36:56.773
Is it the smell of dirt,

665
00:36:56.797 --> 00:36:59.207
since you came from the bottom up?

666
00:37:01.177 --> 00:37:03.462
- Father.
- "Father"?

667
00:37:06.807 --> 00:37:09.426
You're funny.

668
00:37:15.691 --> 00:37:16.877
Listen carefully.

669
00:37:16.901 --> 00:37:20.062
You two will break up within a week.

670
00:37:20.404 --> 00:37:24.900
And Ha-young will marry into
Dosang Group as I'd planned.

671
00:37:28.162 --> 00:37:30.072
"Father"?

672
00:37:30.122 --> 00:37:34.701
Someone like you can never call me "Father."

673
00:37:35.211 --> 00:37:38.664
Though you must not understand
since you don't have a father.

674
00:37:54.230 --> 00:37:55.874
Kang-ho.

675
00:37:55.898 --> 00:37:57.933
What's all this?

676
00:37:58.109 --> 00:38:01.561
Don't tell me you're seeing another woman.

677
00:38:03.239 --> 00:38:05.759
Hold on! My foot.

678
00:38:05.783 --> 00:38:08.887
I hurt my toe today.

679
00:38:08.911 --> 00:38:10.946
Let me in for just a minute.

680
00:38:16.669 --> 00:38:20.539
Kang-ho. It's not true, right?

681
00:38:22.883 --> 00:38:24.027
Ta-da.

682
00:38:24.051 --> 00:38:26.670
I even got you a birthday gift.

683
00:38:27.930 --> 00:38:31.049
- Go home.
- How are you so heartless?

684
00:38:31.559 --> 00:38:33.245
Are you really ending it with me?

685
00:38:33.269 --> 00:38:35.580
I'm doing this not to do that.

686
00:38:35.604 --> 00:38:38.542
But if you keep doing this,
it'll hinder my plan.

687
00:38:38.566 --> 00:38:40.183
Your plan?

688
00:38:40.735 --> 00:38:42.561
What is it?

689
00:38:46.907 --> 00:38:48.135
{\an8}<i><font color="#ffa07a">DNA Test Result</font></i>

690
00:38:48.159 --> 00:38:51.722
Corporate sales, which were to be
reduced to the global economic downturn,

691
00:38:51.746 --> 00:38:55.365
have actually increased by
21.5% compared to last year.

692
00:38:55.416 --> 00:38:58.785
Here are the documents I told you about on...

693
00:39:08.512 --> 00:39:10.198
{\an8}<i><font color="#ffa07a">Probability of Paternity: 99.9%</font></i>

694
00:39:10.222 --> 00:39:12.883
<i>Home run!</i>

695
00:39:14.310 --> 00:39:16.705
This is a true home run.

696
00:39:16.729 --> 00:39:19.931
A walk-off grand slam with two outs.

697
00:39:21.400 --> 00:39:22.794
So you're saying...

698
00:39:22.818 --> 00:39:27.090
Hwang Soo-hyun gave birth to Oh Tae-soo's baby?

699
00:39:27.114 --> 00:39:28.133
Correct.

700
00:39:28.157 --> 00:39:29.900
That idiot.

701
00:39:30.534 --> 00:39:32.512
He had no idea what was coming...

702
00:39:32.536 --> 00:39:34.988
when he betrayed me for Dosang Group.

703
00:39:35.039 --> 00:39:36.808
So what if he steals a base?

704
00:39:36.832 --> 00:39:39.076
He just hit into a double play.

705
00:39:42.129 --> 00:39:45.692
He doesn't know about the child yet.

706
00:39:45.716 --> 00:39:49.821
She was afraid he'd harm her
and the child if he found out.

707
00:39:49.845 --> 00:39:53.325
So she quit and hid as soon as
she found out about her pregnancy.

708
00:39:53.349 --> 00:39:57.385
A secret about him he doesn't even know exists.

709
00:40:01.524 --> 00:40:03.335
This is...

710
00:40:03.359 --> 00:40:05.462
very valuable information.

711
00:40:05.486 --> 00:40:07.104
Right?

712
00:40:08.406 --> 00:40:12.818
By the way, why are you giving me this?

713
00:40:14.328 --> 00:40:17.155
Isn't that why you took me in?

714
00:40:17.665 --> 00:40:19.935
If you have the future President in your hands,

715
00:40:19.959 --> 00:40:22.786
Woobyeok Group will be invincible.

716
00:40:23.462 --> 00:40:24.996
However,

717
00:40:25.047 --> 00:40:27.749
this isn't the original paper.

718
00:40:28.092 --> 00:40:32.129
You must want a favor from me.

719
00:40:35.641 --> 00:40:38.426
Please take me in as your real son.

720
00:40:39.813 --> 00:40:40.789
What did you say?

721
00:40:40.813 --> 00:40:45.517
I want to become your legal son.

722
00:40:45.985 --> 00:40:47.838
Then as your son,

723
00:40:47.862 --> 00:40:50.647
I'll marry Oh Tae-soo's daughter.

724
00:40:50.781 --> 00:40:52.634
You'll have Oh Tae-soo.

725
00:40:52.658 --> 00:40:54.943
Oh Tae-soo will have me.

726
00:40:55.453 --> 00:40:57.904
And I'll have a father.

727
00:40:58.956 --> 00:41:01.852
None of us will be able to betray one another.

728
00:41:01.876 --> 00:41:03.827
We'll become a true family.

729
00:41:13.137 --> 00:41:15.547
What if I refuse?

730
00:41:16.682 --> 00:41:20.093
What can a son who's been
abandoned by his father do?

731
00:41:21.687 --> 00:41:23.847
I'll have to find a new father.

732
00:41:32.031 --> 00:41:35.942
A father never abandons his child.

733
00:41:38.954 --> 00:41:42.726
She was a smart secretary of mine
who knew how the company worked.

734
00:41:42.750 --> 00:41:44.102
I entrusted you with her,

735
00:41:44.126 --> 00:41:47.272
so you'd find a way to save my company.

736
00:41:47.296 --> 00:41:50.901
But instead, you knocked her up.

737
00:41:50.925 --> 00:41:53.126
Where is Hwang Soo-hyun?

738
00:41:54.011 --> 00:41:58.840
How will you lead the
country if you're this slow?

739
00:41:59.099 --> 00:42:03.747
Hwang Soo-hyun isn't the one you should meet.

740
00:42:03.771 --> 00:42:05.639
It's Choi Kang-ho.

741
00:42:06.398 --> 00:42:08.376
If that kid takes this information...

742
00:42:08.400 --> 00:42:11.046
and sides with the Bareun Hanguk Party,

743
00:42:11.070 --> 00:42:14.481
it'll be the end for both of us.

744
00:42:16.033 --> 00:42:17.052
Let's be honest.

745
00:42:17.076 --> 00:42:22.307
We've gotten our hands
dirty for the past 30 years.

746
00:42:22.331 --> 00:42:23.865
Don't you agree?

747
00:42:24.500 --> 00:42:26.701
Judging by...

748
00:42:26.835 --> 00:42:29.397
how he even found out about Hwang Soo-hyun,

749
00:42:29.421 --> 00:42:33.959
he must have many cards up his sleeve.

750
00:42:34.218 --> 00:42:37.420
I heard you opposed his
relationship with your daughter.

751
00:42:37.513 --> 00:42:42.050
It seems to have hurt his pride greatly.

752
00:42:42.977 --> 00:42:48.306
I believe that's when he
started digging up dirt on you.

753
00:42:49.024 --> 00:42:53.255
How about we let them get back together first?

754
00:42:53.279 --> 00:42:55.549
As for the parts you believe he lacks,

755
00:42:55.573 --> 00:42:57.133
I'll fill them in.

756
00:42:57.157 --> 00:42:59.317
What do you mean?

757
00:42:59.910 --> 00:43:01.695
I'm going to...

758
00:43:01.829 --> 00:43:04.322
adopt Choi Kang-ho as my son...

759
00:43:04.415 --> 00:43:07.158
who'll have the right to inherit my business.

760
00:43:09.503 --> 00:43:14.582
Will you get rid of the original copy
of the DNA test result in front of me?

761
00:43:15.676 --> 00:43:19.614
Come on. Getting rid of that
paper won't change anything.

762
00:43:19.638 --> 00:43:21.157
Right?

763
00:43:21.181 --> 00:43:25.010
He'll get rid of them like they never existed.

764
00:43:25.978 --> 00:43:27.846
My son will do that.

765
00:43:30.190 --> 00:43:31.850
Right?

766
00:43:42.911 --> 00:43:45.822
You'll be safer there than in Korea.

767
00:43:52.463 --> 00:43:55.206
No one will be able to find you.

768
00:43:57.426 --> 00:44:00.712
Don't worry about it. It'll all work out.

769
00:44:00.929 --> 00:44:02.839
Thank you for the drink.

770
00:44:55.401 --> 00:44:57.352
I took care of it.

771
00:45:02.825 --> 00:45:06.528
We finally have our own nail salon!

772
00:45:08.330 --> 00:45:10.183
<i><font color="#ffff00">Nail & Nail</font></i>

773
00:45:10.207 --> 00:45:12.784
Sun-young...

774
00:45:13.627 --> 00:45:16.162
Why are you crying?

775
00:45:21.009 --> 00:45:25.115
Why would you cry on such a delightful day?

776
00:45:25.139 --> 00:45:28.716
You're the one who cried first.

777
00:45:30.602 --> 00:45:32.387
You know what?

778
00:45:33.021 --> 00:45:35.348
I'm going to make a ton of money,

779
00:45:35.649 --> 00:45:39.185
and bring my kids back.

780
00:45:39.903 --> 00:45:43.633
I'm going to buy them...

781
00:45:43.657 --> 00:45:45.510
whatever food they want,

782
00:45:45.534 --> 00:45:48.736
and dress them in all the pretty clothes.

783
00:45:49.204 --> 00:45:50.864
I will.

784
00:45:55.919 --> 00:45:58.440
It's not smelly, right?

785
00:45:58.464 --> 00:46:00.525
It's thanks to our homemade <i>doenjang.</i>

786
00:46:00.549 --> 00:46:03.918
Have some aged kimchi too. It's tasty.

787
00:46:07.973 --> 00:46:10.160
It would've been perfect if there was skate.

788
00:46:10.184 --> 00:46:12.662
Skate and celebrations go hand in hand.

789
00:46:12.686 --> 00:46:15.832
I'm sure someone will bring some.

790
00:46:15.856 --> 00:46:18.918
Gosh, do you hear those two kids?

791
00:46:18.942 --> 00:46:21.337
Kids these days learn so quickly.

792
00:46:21.361 --> 00:46:25.273
They learn too quickly.

793
00:46:25.782 --> 00:46:28.818
I suddenly miss my late mother.

794
00:46:32.372 --> 00:46:33.981
- It'll be fun...
- This is too salty.

795
00:46:34.005 --> 00:46:36.644
...to hit a ball with this.

796
00:46:36.668 --> 00:46:38.188
This is too bland.

797
00:46:38.212 --> 00:46:39.746
Do you want some?

798
00:46:41.465 --> 00:46:42.901
Even a dog doesn't want it.

799
00:46:42.925 --> 00:46:46.279
Goodness. Young-soon is so lucky.

800
00:46:46.303 --> 00:46:53.051
She went through so much
to raise her son by herself.

801
00:46:53.519 --> 00:46:57.415
And now he's a prosecutor and
an assemblyman's son-in-law.

802
00:46:57.439 --> 00:46:59.125
Things are looking up for her.

803
00:46:59.149 --> 00:47:02.378
It's more than just that.

804
00:47:02.402 --> 00:47:05.230
Her social status will change.

805
00:47:05.405 --> 00:47:07.842
Social status, my foot.

806
00:47:07.866 --> 00:47:11.804
And if that's the case, she
should've hired a catering service.

807
00:47:11.828 --> 00:47:13.681
Look at this.

808
00:47:13.705 --> 00:47:16.518
How will we feed all those
people with that much meat?

809
00:47:16.542 --> 00:47:20.146
We can slaughter a pig if need be.

810
00:47:20.170 --> 00:47:24.832
There's no need to worry about
that when she has a pig farm.

811
00:47:25.259 --> 00:47:26.361
Nice one.

812
00:47:26.385 --> 00:47:27.654
You must be tired.

813
00:47:27.678 --> 00:47:29.572
- Hello.
- Let me do it.

814
00:47:29.596 --> 00:47:30.740
Gosh, you reek.

815
00:47:30.764 --> 00:47:32.492
Wash up.

816
00:47:32.516 --> 00:47:34.786
Yes, leave this up to us.

817
00:47:34.810 --> 00:47:37.247
Get dressed up.

818
00:47:37.271 --> 00:47:41.209
Will you greet the assemblyman's
daughter while looking like that?

819
00:47:41.233 --> 00:47:42.934
You little...!

820
00:47:43.193 --> 00:47:45.046
I told you not to tell anyone.

821
00:47:45.070 --> 00:47:47.590
She also told me to keep it a secret.

822
00:47:47.614 --> 00:47:49.399
Right.

823
00:47:49.908 --> 00:47:52.527
Well, it's good news, so...

824
00:47:53.579 --> 00:47:56.266
By the way, who's the assemblyman?

825
00:47:56.290 --> 00:48:00.770
My son's colleague told me the news,

826
00:48:00.794 --> 00:48:03.773
but I don't know who it is exactly.

827
00:48:03.797 --> 00:48:07.694
Anyway, please don't say
these things in front of Kang-ho.

828
00:48:07.718 --> 00:48:09.612
- Okay?
- Of course.

829
00:48:09.636 --> 00:48:12.198
It's great that he's marrying
an assemblyman's daughter.

830
00:48:12.222 --> 00:48:16.592
But honestly, it's not great news for us.

831
00:48:16.852 --> 00:48:19.914
Honestly, we didn't benefit from Kang-ho's...

832
00:48:19.938 --> 00:48:23.683
going to law school and
becoming a prosecutor, did we?

833
00:48:24.693 --> 00:48:26.129
Darn it.

834
00:48:26.153 --> 00:48:28.590
We could've gotten that done at a mill.

835
00:48:28.614 --> 00:48:33.011
Look at that old man overworking himself.

836
00:48:33.035 --> 00:48:34.777
At that age, he...

837
00:48:35.370 --> 00:48:37.348
Never mind. Keep going.

838
00:48:37.372 --> 00:48:41.811
You weren't talking about me, were you?

839
00:48:41.835 --> 00:48:43.605
Hey, Sung-ae!

840
00:48:43.629 --> 00:48:46.232
- Go ahead and hit.
- She's bitter about...

841
00:48:46.256 --> 00:48:48.583
how Sam-sik was incarcerated for theft.

842
00:48:48.759 --> 00:48:52.864
She begged Kang-ho not
to put her son behind bars,

843
00:48:52.888 --> 00:48:55.575
but he refused to listen.

844
00:48:55.599 --> 00:48:58.926
She's still bitter about that.

845
00:48:59.603 --> 00:49:00.622
Just leave her alone.

846
00:49:00.646 --> 00:49:02.305
Okay.

847
00:49:04.775 --> 00:49:09.020
What's the big deal about marrying
an assemblyman's daughter?

848
00:49:13.492 --> 00:49:15.094
I should go home.

849
00:49:15.118 --> 00:49:19.572
My dog hasn't been eating
much due to her labor pains.

850
00:49:20.540 --> 00:49:22.575
When's the date?

851
00:49:22.834 --> 00:49:26.147
Since she's spotting,
it'll be today or tomorrow.

852
00:49:26.171 --> 00:49:28.915
No, I'm talking about Sam-sik.

853
00:49:30.258 --> 00:49:35.046
I'm going to ask Kang-ho to help
him get a job when he comes today.

854
00:49:37.349 --> 00:49:40.093
Where are the mung beans? There they are.

855
00:49:40.686 --> 00:49:41.704
Move.

856
00:49:41.728 --> 00:49:44.430
I know Kang-ho likes mung bean pancakes.

857
00:49:58.745 --> 00:49:59.721
<i><font color="#ffa07a">Sillim Fresh Raw Fish</font></i>

858
00:50:03.083 --> 00:50:04.668
{\an8}<i><font color="#ffa07a">Reject</font></i>

859
00:50:14.177 --> 00:50:16.295
My head hurts.

860
00:50:24.479 --> 00:50:25.957
You didn't have to come.

861
00:50:25.981 --> 00:50:28.683
I should meet her at least once.

862
00:50:28.859 --> 00:50:31.212
After all, she's your mother.

863
00:50:31.236 --> 00:50:35.356
And I can drive when you feel tired.

864
00:50:35.741 --> 00:50:37.525
Oh, right.

865
00:50:37.868 --> 00:50:40.304
I'm just going to get a five-carat diamond ring.

866
00:50:40.328 --> 00:50:43.239
Smaller ones are trendier these days.

867
00:50:44.291 --> 00:50:47.854
Only those who want to come off as wealthy...

868
00:50:47.878 --> 00:50:50.496
go for big rings.

869
00:50:51.173 --> 00:50:53.958
And my dad's presidential
election is coming up too.

870
00:50:59.139 --> 00:51:01.132
Darn it.

871
00:51:05.979 --> 00:51:07.457
<i>What?</i>

872
00:51:07.481 --> 00:51:08.791
You got half a carat?

873
00:51:08.815 --> 00:51:12.894
Only big department stores in Seoul have them.

874
00:51:13.195 --> 00:51:16.507
- There's a warranty in there too.
- A warranty?

875
00:51:16.531 --> 00:51:18.384
In there. Underneath.

876
00:51:18.408 --> 00:51:21.846
Come on. Stay still.

877
00:51:21.870 --> 00:51:25.490
The gem sure looks huge.

878
00:51:25.582 --> 00:51:27.560
Goodness. Half a carat?

879
00:51:27.584 --> 00:51:29.729
Wait. Don't touch it.

880
00:51:29.753 --> 00:51:32.538
- I wasn't going to.
- You look nice.

881
00:51:34.674 --> 00:51:39.921
It would've been wonderful if Kang-ho
and Mi-joo had ended up together.

882
00:51:41.056 --> 00:51:43.201
Remember?

883
00:51:43.225 --> 00:51:45.927
When they were kids,

884
00:51:45.977 --> 00:51:48.998
we promised to become in-laws.

885
00:51:49.022 --> 00:51:51.834
Your daughter is happily married in the U.S.

886
00:51:51.858 --> 00:51:52.919
What are you saying?

887
00:51:52.943 --> 00:51:55.269
I'm just saying.

888
00:51:56.279 --> 00:51:58.064
By the way,

889
00:51:58.698 --> 00:52:01.427
why did you get this when
they haven't set a date yet?

890
00:52:01.451 --> 00:52:05.363
I also got a ring before I got married.

891
00:52:05.413 --> 00:52:10.743
He brought a pig with the ring
around its neck when he proposed.

892
00:52:13.213 --> 00:52:14.774
Gosh.

893
00:52:14.798 --> 00:52:18.042
He would've been delighted if he'd been alive.

894
00:52:23.932 --> 00:52:26.008
You're all done.

895
00:52:31.356 --> 00:52:35.393
You look like Brooke Shields.

896
00:52:36.403 --> 00:52:40.216
No wonder Sam-sik is dexterous.
He takes after his mother.

897
00:52:40.240 --> 00:52:43.985
Why are you bringing up his dexterity right now?

898
00:52:44.286 --> 00:52:46.889
What is this? Is it a back-handed compliment?

899
00:52:46.913 --> 00:52:49.934
What are you talking about?

900
00:52:49.958 --> 00:52:53.396
It's only natural for your
child to take after you.

901
00:52:53.420 --> 00:52:57.525
Sure, but we're talking about Sam-sik.

902
00:52:57.549 --> 00:52:59.443
What do you think?

903
00:52:59.467 --> 00:53:01.586
This is a set.

904
00:53:05.974 --> 00:53:09.328
Goodness, you look gorgeous.

905
00:53:09.352 --> 00:53:12.930
You look like a forsythia.

906
00:53:13.315 --> 00:53:15.167
- Do I look okay?
- Yes.

907
00:53:15.191 --> 00:53:18.212
She has a good eye for
picking out the right colors.

908
00:53:18.236 --> 00:53:19.338
Tell me about it.

909
00:53:19.362 --> 00:53:21.883
How did you think of picking such a color?

910
00:53:21.907 --> 00:53:25.526
Vivid colors are trendy now.

911
00:53:25.577 --> 00:53:27.638
I don't want her to think...

912
00:53:27.662 --> 00:53:30.141
I'm a hillbilly with no fashion sense.

913
00:53:30.165 --> 00:53:33.603
How dare a woman look down on her mother-in-law?

914
00:53:33.627 --> 00:53:35.104
Who cares who her father is?

915
00:53:35.128 --> 00:53:36.939
Reject her if you don't like her.

916
00:53:36.963 --> 00:53:39.525
- Goodness.
- She's right.

917
00:53:39.549 --> 00:53:43.362
I'm telling you, whoever and whatever it may be,

918
00:53:43.386 --> 00:53:46.490
you need to show them who's boss from the start.

919
00:53:46.514 --> 00:53:49.702
That way, they won't cause problems.

920
00:53:49.726 --> 00:53:52.204
Be confident. Okay?

921
00:53:52.228 --> 00:53:53.789
Okay.

922
00:53:53.813 --> 00:53:56.250
<i>Young-soon, come out!</i>

923
00:53:56.274 --> 00:53:58.544
<i>I can't seem to find the drinks.</i>

924
00:53:58.568 --> 00:54:00.353
Coming!

925
00:54:01.821 --> 00:54:05.024
Doesn't she look like a pickled radish?

926
00:54:06.994 --> 00:54:07.970
She's gone.

927
00:54:07.994 --> 00:54:10.655
Her hair looks great, though.

928
00:54:10.705 --> 00:54:13.115
I think she'll be looked down on.

929
00:54:13.500 --> 00:54:14.644
Right?

930
00:54:14.668 --> 00:54:18.731
- Pickled radish!
- Pickled radish!

931
00:54:18.755 --> 00:54:20.650
- Pickled radish!
- Pickled radish!

932
00:54:20.674 --> 00:54:24.070
- Goodness. We have no pickled radish.
- Kids always tell the truth.

933
00:54:24.094 --> 00:54:25.404
Drink slowly.

934
00:54:25.428 --> 00:54:26.864
Young-soon.

935
00:54:26.888 --> 00:54:29.659
Have a drink with us.

936
00:54:29.683 --> 00:54:30.826
Sit.

937
00:54:30.850 --> 00:54:34.845
I'll eat after I meet Kang-ho's fiancée.

938
00:54:34.938 --> 00:54:35.957
Right.

939
00:54:35.981 --> 00:54:38.876
It's your first time meeting her, right?

940
00:54:38.900 --> 00:54:40.753
- Yes.
- Gosh.

941
00:54:40.777 --> 00:54:44.674
Kang-ho shouldn't be like this to his mother.

942
00:54:44.698 --> 00:54:47.149
It's understandable.

943
00:54:47.242 --> 00:54:50.012
His mother worked so hard to raise him,

944
00:54:50.036 --> 00:54:54.767
so how could he only now
introduce his fiancée to her?

945
00:54:54.791 --> 00:54:57.436
- He's very busy.
- Right.

946
00:54:57.460 --> 00:55:02.650
Honestly, I'm elated that
he's visiting us today.

947
00:55:02.674 --> 00:55:03.776
Of course.

948
00:55:03.800 --> 00:55:05.876
- Hold on.
- What?

949
00:55:06.136 --> 00:55:08.739
Do you think he's coming here...

950
00:55:08.763 --> 00:55:11.632
to take Young-soon to Seoul?

951
00:55:12.142 --> 00:55:13.119
Seoul?

952
00:55:13.143 --> 00:55:15.579
Think about it. Jong-ho did that too.

953
00:55:15.603 --> 00:55:18.666
He took his parents to
Seoul before getting married.

954
00:55:18.690 --> 00:55:21.335
- You're right.
- You're right.

955
00:55:21.359 --> 00:55:23.921
That could happen. So she's going to Seoul?

956
00:55:23.945 --> 00:55:25.006
It makes sense.

957
00:55:25.030 --> 00:55:27.967
After all, his future
father-in-law is an assemblyman.

958
00:55:27.991 --> 00:55:31.736
Kang-ho wouldn't let his mother
keep living here all by herself.

959
00:55:31.995 --> 00:55:33.681
What now?

960
00:55:33.705 --> 00:55:35.391
Is this goodbye for us?

961
00:55:35.415 --> 00:55:39.061
This is great.

962
00:55:39.085 --> 00:55:41.439
What will happen to your farm then?

963
00:55:41.463 --> 00:55:43.733
Leave your potato farm to me.

964
00:55:43.757 --> 00:55:45.526
Oh, dear. Hold on.

965
00:55:45.550 --> 00:55:47.501
Goodness.

966
00:55:48.261 --> 00:55:53.367
You'll still help Sam-sik get a job, right?

967
00:55:53.391 --> 00:55:54.452
You will, right?

968
00:55:54.476 --> 00:55:56.037
- Young-soon.
- Sung-ae.

969
00:55:56.061 --> 00:55:59.415
Oh, no. Is this farewell?

970
00:55:59.439 --> 00:56:00.624
He's here!

971
00:56:00.648 --> 00:56:02.543
Kang-ho has arrived from Seoul!

972
00:56:02.567 --> 00:56:05.755
- He's here.
- Kang-ho? He's here!

973
00:56:05.779 --> 00:56:07.006
- Kang-ho!
- Hurry up!

974
00:56:07.030 --> 00:56:08.632
- Kang-ho!
- Kang-ho!

975
00:56:08.656 --> 00:56:10.983
- Kang-ho!
- Kang-ho!

976
00:56:12.160 --> 00:56:13.804
- Goodness. Kang-ho!
- Goodness.

977
00:56:13.828 --> 00:56:14.764
Goodness.

978
00:56:14.788 --> 00:56:16.515
- Oh, my!
- Goodness!

979
00:56:16.539 --> 00:56:17.892
She's so pretty.

980
00:56:17.916 --> 00:56:20.117
How pretty.

981
00:56:22.128 --> 00:56:24.163
You're here.

982
00:56:25.256 --> 00:56:27.833
I'm the village head.

983
00:56:28.343 --> 00:56:30.002
Hello.

984
00:56:33.139 --> 00:56:36.660
We sincerely welcome you two to Jou-ri,

985
00:56:36.684 --> 00:56:40.456
a village with clear water...

986
00:56:40.480 --> 00:56:43.793
and good-hearted people.

987
00:56:43.817 --> 00:56:46.545
There's no body of water here.

988
00:56:46.569 --> 00:56:49.673
And why do you sound like an AI?

989
00:56:49.697 --> 00:56:51.050
You're unbelievable.

990
00:56:51.074 --> 00:56:55.304
Everyone, this is Prosecutor Choi Kang-ho...

991
00:56:55.328 --> 00:56:58.432
and his fiancée, an assemblyman's daughter.

992
00:56:58.456 --> 00:56:59.350
Let's all bow... No.

993
00:56:59.374 --> 00:57:01.727
Give them a round of applause.

994
00:57:01.751 --> 00:57:04.787
I told you not to mention her father.

995
00:57:05.213 --> 00:57:07.191
It must've been a long trip.

996
00:57:07.215 --> 00:57:08.609
Come on in.

997
00:57:08.633 --> 00:57:10.402
- Come on.
- Go in.

998
00:57:10.426 --> 00:57:13.003
- Goodness.
- Hello.

999
00:57:13.388 --> 00:57:16.117
- She's pretty.
- Behave.

1000
00:57:16.141 --> 00:57:17.535
Come on.

1001
00:57:17.559 --> 00:57:18.869
You must be hungry.

1002
00:57:18.893 --> 00:57:21.288
Let's eat first.

1003
00:57:21.312 --> 00:57:23.624
- I have something to tell you.
- Gosh.

1004
00:57:23.648 --> 00:57:25.376
What's the rush?

1005
00:57:25.400 --> 00:57:28.978
Let's eat first and talk later.

1006
00:57:29.028 --> 00:57:30.673
- Come here.
- Ma'am.

1007
00:57:30.697 --> 00:57:33.524
You're so beautiful.

1008
00:57:33.783 --> 00:57:36.720
- How about you sing a song?
- That's a good idea.

1009
00:57:36.744 --> 00:57:38.597
- Sing for us!
- Sing for us!

1010
00:57:38.621 --> 00:57:40.558
- Sing for us!
- Sing for us!

1011
00:57:40.582 --> 00:57:42.518
- Sing for us!
- Sing for us!

1012
00:57:42.542 --> 00:57:44.186
- Sing for us!
- Sir.

1013
00:57:44.210 --> 00:57:48.065
♫ <i>You can't get married if you can't sing</i> ♫

1014
00:57:48.089 --> 00:57:51.527
♫ <i>You're so mean</i> ♫
Gosh, this is embarrassing.

1015
00:57:51.551 --> 00:57:53.571
So mean!
♫ <i>If you can't get married</i> ♫

1016
00:57:53.595 --> 00:57:54.697
Kang-ho.
♫ <i>You can't</i> ♫

1017
00:57:54.721 --> 00:57:56.714
I have something to say!

1018
00:57:58.099 --> 00:58:00.384
- Goodness.
- Go inside.

1019
00:58:04.522 --> 00:58:08.058
Come in. Goodness.

1020
00:58:08.818 --> 00:58:11.061
Last night,

1021
00:58:11.196 --> 00:58:14.425
your father visited me in my dreams.

1022
00:58:14.449 --> 00:58:16.775
Have a seat.

1023
00:58:19.579 --> 00:58:25.019
He was silent and glared
at me like he was upset.

1024
00:58:25.043 --> 00:58:29.023
I thought long and hard about
why he was sulking so much.

1025
00:58:29.047 --> 00:58:33.792
He must've been jealous that
I'd be the only one to witness this.

1026
00:58:35.261 --> 00:58:37.588
Gosh, you're beautiful.

1027
00:58:38.056 --> 00:58:39.658
How old are you?

1028
00:58:39.682 --> 00:58:41.368
I'm 27.

1029
00:58:41.392 --> 00:58:43.928
You have the perfect age gap.

1030
00:58:44.687 --> 00:58:47.348
Hold on.

1031
00:58:55.490 --> 00:58:59.026
I got this at the biggest jewelry shop in town.

1032
00:59:02.997 --> 00:59:04.990
They're diamonds.

1033
00:59:05.583 --> 00:59:07.326
I see.

1034
00:59:09.754 --> 00:59:11.607
Can you wait outside?

1035
00:59:11.631 --> 00:59:12.816
Okay.

1036
00:59:12.840 --> 00:59:15.209
Why?

1037
00:59:25.436 --> 00:59:27.596
I know that brand.

1038
00:59:27.647 --> 00:59:28.958
You know...

1039
00:59:28.982 --> 00:59:30.125
Vutton!

1040
00:59:30.149 --> 00:59:32.726
- It's a luxury handbag.
- I see.

1041
00:59:33.695 --> 00:59:37.007
What are those boxes?

1042
00:59:37.031 --> 00:59:40.511
It says "fur..."

1043
00:59:40.535 --> 00:59:42.721
As in animal fur?

1044
00:59:42.745 --> 00:59:45.724
Animal fur? Maybe it's a mink coat.

1045
00:59:45.748 --> 00:59:46.892
It could be.

1046
00:59:46.916 --> 00:59:49.270
I heard they skin minks alive.

1047
00:59:49.294 --> 00:59:54.039
Don't say something so horrific.

1048
00:59:54.132 --> 00:59:56.819
By the way, what are those boxes?

1049
00:59:56.843 --> 01:00:01.463
Do you think they're for us?

1050
01:00:01.889 --> 01:00:03.966
What are you doing there?

1051
01:00:15.528 --> 01:00:17.771
Goodness.

1052
01:00:17.905 --> 01:00:23.304
Come to think of it, your fiancée
was born in the Year of the Pig.

1053
01:00:23.328 --> 01:00:25.598
It must be destiny.

1054
01:00:25.622 --> 01:00:29.393
Who am I? I'm a pig farmer.

1055
01:00:29.417 --> 01:00:33.579
She was destined to marry
into our family, right?

1056
01:00:41.346 --> 01:00:43.088
What is this?

1057
01:00:50.480 --> 01:00:52.723
"Adoption Agreement"?

1058
01:00:53.358 --> 01:00:54.793
What is this?

1059
01:00:54.817 --> 01:00:57.770
Are you going to adopt a child?

1060
01:00:59.405 --> 01:01:00.466
Why?

1061
01:01:00.490 --> 01:01:02.384
She can't get pregnant?

1062
01:01:02.408 --> 01:01:06.362
I'll be adopted by Chairman Song
who's been raising me all along.

1063
01:01:06.871 --> 01:01:09.323
Please stamp your seal there.

1064
01:01:12.585 --> 01:01:16.315
- What?
- Be quiet.

1065
01:01:16.339 --> 01:01:17.983
What...?

1066
01:01:18.007 --> 01:01:20.542
What are you saying?

1067
01:01:21.719 --> 01:01:25.172
Who raised you? Who's adopting you?

1068
01:01:26.099 --> 01:01:28.035
I'm your mom.

1069
01:01:28.059 --> 01:01:30.344
I gave birth to you.

1070
01:01:30.395 --> 01:01:32.790
What are you talking about?

1071
01:01:32.814 --> 01:01:34.958
I'm going to become Chairman Song's son,

1072
01:01:34.982 --> 01:01:38.811
inherit his business, and become
an assemblyman's son-in-law.

1073
01:01:40.196 --> 01:01:41.814
Wait.

1074
01:01:42.407 --> 01:01:47.429
Wait, Kang-ho. What are you talking about?

1075
01:01:47.453 --> 01:01:50.099
I get that money and power are great.

1076
01:01:50.123 --> 01:01:52.351
But you can't cut ties with your mom.

1077
01:01:52.375 --> 01:01:55.035
Isn't this what you wanted?

1078
01:01:57.338 --> 01:01:58.956
What...?

1079
01:02:07.056 --> 01:02:09.642
{\an8}<i><font color="#ffa07a">Consenting Party: Jin Young-soon
Signature or Seal</font></i>

1080
01:02:47.638 --> 01:02:49.339
All right.

1081
01:02:52.393 --> 01:02:54.928
I'll always be your mom.

1082
01:02:56.731 --> 01:03:00.976
This piece of paper won't matter.

1083
01:03:01.819 --> 01:03:04.855
I'm happy as long as you are.

1084
01:03:15.875 --> 01:03:18.118
Let me ask you one question.

1085
01:03:18.669 --> 01:03:21.121
Did you propose the idea?

1086
01:03:21.380 --> 01:03:22.941
You didn't, right?

1087
01:03:22.965 --> 01:03:24.401
He did, right?

1088
01:03:24.425 --> 01:03:28.071
You didn't want to, but he forced
you because he needs you, right?

1089
01:03:28.095 --> 01:03:30.297
Am I right?

1090
01:03:56.624 --> 01:03:59.326
Wait.

1091
01:03:59.794 --> 01:04:01.480
Kang-ho.

1092
01:04:01.504 --> 01:04:04.331
I can't let you go like this.

1093
01:04:06.300 --> 01:04:09.044
Have some food before you go.

1094
01:04:12.765 --> 01:04:14.341
Food?

1095
01:04:15.601 --> 01:04:18.178
You're inviting me to eat,

1096
01:04:18.938 --> 01:04:22.724
when I've never been able
to enjoy a meal with you?

1097
01:04:29.824 --> 01:04:31.677
Then take this.

1098
01:04:31.701 --> 01:04:34.346
Take this with you.

1099
01:04:34.370 --> 01:04:37.266
Why won't you take this?

1100
01:04:37.290 --> 01:04:41.270
I get that you're embarrassed
by me since I'm a poor hillbilly.

1101
01:04:41.294 --> 01:04:42.729
But why won't you take this?

1102
01:04:42.753 --> 01:04:44.356
These are all brand new.

1103
01:04:44.380 --> 01:04:47.317
They sell these at big
department stores in Seoul.

1104
01:04:47.341 --> 01:04:49.820
There's a warranty too. Kang...

1105
01:04:49.844 --> 01:04:51.572
Kang-ho...

1106
01:04:51.596 --> 01:04:54.881
- Does this make sense?
- I don't know.

1107
01:04:59.270 --> 01:05:01.388
Goodness.

1108
01:05:03.566 --> 01:05:06.351
Wait. Kang-ho.

1109
01:05:07.069 --> 01:05:08.854
Kang-ho.

1110
01:05:21.834 --> 01:05:22.936
Kang-ho.

1111
01:05:22.960 --> 01:05:24.897
Wait.

1112
01:05:24.921 --> 01:05:26.899
They're mung bean pancakes, your favorite.

1113
01:05:26.923 --> 01:05:29.124
Have some on your way, okay?

1114
01:05:34.805 --> 01:05:37.507
Kang-ho!

1115
01:05:37.642 --> 01:05:41.038
What an impudent punk!

1116
01:05:41.062 --> 01:05:43.597
Goodness.

1117
01:05:45.441 --> 01:05:47.544
Look at this handbag.

1118
01:05:47.568 --> 01:05:51.340
She must have good taste
because she lives in Seoul.

1119
01:05:51.364 --> 01:05:53.717
Goodness. This is very light.

1120
01:05:53.741 --> 01:05:55.817
I can barely feel it.

1121
01:05:56.118 --> 01:05:57.903
By the way,

1122
01:05:58.037 --> 01:05:59.973
if Chairman Song adopts him,

1123
01:05:59.997 --> 01:06:02.699
does that mean he'll be Song Kang-ho now?

1124
01:06:08.506 --> 01:06:11.208
Don't worry about me.

1125
01:06:11.801 --> 01:06:13.627
Gosh.

1126
01:06:13.719 --> 01:06:17.157
I've been running on an
empty stomach. I'm hungry now.

1127
01:06:17.181 --> 01:06:18.784
Why are you out here?

1128
01:06:18.808 --> 01:06:21.828
We have lots of food inside. Go inside.

1129
01:06:21.852 --> 01:06:22.996
Go inside.

1130
01:06:23.020 --> 01:06:24.581
- Okay.
- Gosh.

1131
01:06:24.605 --> 01:06:27.099
Go away, kids.

1132
01:06:27.608 --> 01:06:30.128
Kids, go play.

1133
01:06:30.152 --> 01:06:31.687
Go.

1134
01:06:43.124 --> 01:06:45.283
The smell is making me carsick.

1135
01:06:50.006 --> 01:06:52.666
Are we really taking that home?

1136
01:06:56.762 --> 01:06:59.214
I hope my clothes won't reek of it.

1137
01:07:07.314 --> 01:07:08.959
Kang-ho.

1138
01:07:08.983 --> 01:07:10.684
Kang-ho.

1139
01:07:11.652 --> 01:07:13.395
Kang-ho...

1140
01:07:35.134 --> 01:07:36.710
Kang-ho.

1141
01:07:49.732 --> 01:07:52.350
Should I drive instead?

1142
01:07:54.403 --> 01:07:56.563
Okay. I'm sorry.

1143
01:08:05.873 --> 01:08:07.574
Kang-ho.

1144
01:08:07.875 --> 01:08:09.576
Are you okay?

1145
01:08:15.216 --> 01:08:17.751
It still reeks.

1146
01:09:08.811 --> 01:09:10.512
Kang-ho.

1147
01:09:11.105 --> 01:09:12.791
No.

1148
01:09:12.815 --> 01:09:14.808
Kang-ho, no...

1149
01:09:15.651 --> 01:09:17.894
No!

1150
01:09:19.947 --> 01:09:22.092
Kang-ho!

1151
01:09:22.116 --> 01:09:25.569
Kang-ho!

1152
01:09:48.559 --> 01:09:51.478
<i><font color="#ffff00">The Good Bad Mother</font></i>

1153
01:10:01.530 --> 01:10:02.716
<i>My son won't die.</i>

1154
01:10:02.740 --> 01:10:05.051
<i>I won't let him die.</i>

1155
01:10:05.075 --> 01:10:06.928
<i>What? Kang-ho?</i>

1156
01:10:06.952 --> 01:10:09.973
<i>- I'm telling you.
- Then what will happen to Kang-ho?</i>

1157
01:10:09.997 --> 01:10:11.740
<i>Just watch and see.</i>

1158
01:10:11.790 --> 01:10:15.395
<i>Our son will walk out of that room.</i>

1159
01:10:15.419 --> 01:10:18.690
{\an8}<i>He'll stand here and look at you.</i>

1160
01:10:18.714 --> 01:10:20.525
{\an8}<i>I'll make sure he does.</i>

1161
01:10:20.549 --> 01:10:23.820
{\an8}<i>I hope you learn English
quickly so we can live together.</i>

1162
01:10:23.844 --> 01:10:25.697
{\an8}<i>That was the worst sin you could commit.</i>

1163
01:10:25.721 --> 01:10:27.073
{\an8}<i>Letting others use you.</i>

1164
01:10:27.097 --> 01:10:29.492
{\an8}<i>My son woke up!</i>

1165
01:10:29.516 --> 01:10:30.994
{\an8}<i>It's me, Mom.</i>

1166
01:10:31.018 --> 01:10:33.386
{\an8}<i>Do you recognize me?</i>

